    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Besu already stores the minimal amount of fields necessary. The changes for Geth and Nethermind were to not store fields that can derived and to not store those fields. E.g. Geth was storing the transaction hash, gas cost, and contract address.\n\nIn Besu we are only storing state root | status, cumulative gas, bloom filter and logs and optionally the revert reason. This is also what Geth is storing with the changes that were made (ignoring the optional revert reason).",
